To be '''sent to Coventry''' is to be ostracised, shunned, or otherwise systematically ignored. The phrase dates from the [[English Civil War]], when a military [[prison]] was located in [[coventry|the city]].

The phrase has been adapted by [[internet forum]] programmers, particularly the popular [[vBulletin]] program which has the "Tachy goes to Coventry" option where a forum administrator can cause a user to be automatically "ignored" by all users (rendering their posts invisible).  

It also has something to do with a British Government decision to knowingly allow Coventry to be bombed during the second world war to protect the identities of British spies in Germany. Thus Coventry was not alerted to the raid by being ignored.

